      • getByIdAndUserId

        public static <T extends ResCloudlet> ResCloudlet getByIdAndUserId(List<T> list,
                                                   int cloudletId,
                                                   int userId)
        Returns a given Cloudlet. This method needs a combination of Cloudlet Id and User Id because each Cloud Users might have exactly same Cloudlet Ids.
        Parameters:
        cloudletId - a Cloudlet Id
        userId - an User Id
        list - the list
        Returns:
        the Cloudlet.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - - if a Cloudlet with specified Id and user id is not in the list.

      • indexOf

        public static <T extends ResCloudlet> int indexOf(List<T> list,
                                  int cloudletId,
                                  int userId)
        Finds the index of a Cloudlet inside the list. This method needs a combination of Cloudlet Id and User Id because each Cloud User might have exactly the same Cloudlet Id.
        Parameters:
        cloudletId - a Cloudlet Id
        userId - an User Id
        list - the list
        Returns:
        the index in this list of the first occurrence of the specified Cloudlet, or -1 if the list does not contain this Cloudlet.

        Move a ResCloudlet object from this linked-list into a specified one.
        Parameters:
        listFrom - the list from
        listTo - the list to
        cloudlet - the cloudlet
        Returns:
        true if the moving operation successful, otherwise return false

      • getPositionById

        public static <T extends ResCloudlet> int getPositionById(List<T> cloudletList,
                                          int id)
        Returns the position of the cloudlet with that id, if it exists. Otherwise -1.
        Parameters:
        cloudletList - - the list of cloudlets.
        id - - the id we search for.
        Returns:
        - the position of the cloudlet with that id, or -1 otherwise.
